##Deep Breath in an outbreak. Got Ta get out of here

Micro Signal Xiezuozheyunshegong

FUNCTION INTRODUCTION: Volunteer Information Management, social worker information management, public welfare information release, social work professional exchange

This article is one of the case interviews conducted by the collaborators in the "Peasant Workers' anti-epidemic Rescue Action" , aiming at quickly identifying the vulnerable groups and their needs in the epidemic situation, and providing reference for the epidemic prevention, control and rescue work, we put it together and share it with you.

Deep breathing in case of an outbreak

A case study of migrant workers'families in difficulty in Foshan (VI)

We have to get out of here
Narrator: a Guang (not his real name) / from Henan Province
Place of employment: Zhuhai
Editor's Note: Kong, 39. Early school dropout, 16-year-old work outside, for many years of coolies, and then came to Zhuhai into a foreign electronic factory, in the assembly line to do general work, has worked for nearly 10 years. The family has two children, all follow the daughter-in-law in Henan Home Primary School, the family rely on a light to work outside the wages of the family.

Everyone knows that urban education is better than rural education, but there is no way

When I was about five, my parents stopped talking to me, so I went to live with my grandfather. After my grandfather died, I had to live with my uncle again. As a child, my uncle lived by selling soles, collecting rags and planting a few Mu of land. My uncle's family also had two children, so we couldn't afford to go to school. Because there was no money to pay tuition fees, I was also kicked out of school, also do not want to owe school tuition fees, no way, not to go. When my father died a few days ago, I went back from other places to take his ashes to his hometown to be buried. Honestly, I don't even remember what my dad looked like.

A Guang volunteers with co-workers in Zhuhai (photo taken in March 2018)

I started working outside at the age of 16. When I first came out, I worked in construction sites, brick yards and other places. I also went to Beijing, Jiangsu and other places. Most of my work was done on construction sites. I also went to the electronics factory in Shenzhen to work as a general worker (ordinary worker) . Then I came to Zhuhai, since I was a kid. Later, when I got married and had a child and only had a daughter, I was able to attend a kindergarten in Zhuhai. Later, when my son was born, I earned money to support my family by myself, and I could not afford to spend much in Zhuhai. My Wife and children had to go home first, and left me alone to work in Zhuhai. Everyone knows that urban education is better than rural education, but there is no way.
If it goes on for months, our lives will be ruined

January 16,2020, I took a high-speed train from Zhuhai to the east of Guangzhou, from Guangzhou by train back home for the New Year. There is no high-speed railway from Guangdong to my hometown. I took a hard seat for 24 hours. Train tickets are hard to buy, before going home I am staring at the mobile phone every day, because the train ticket is cheap, 177.5 yuan, but also to save money, if the bus 600-700 yuan, more expensive.

When I got home, I had not heard of the epidemic until the first day of the Lunar New Year, when the village pulled a red banner, but also through loudspeakers to publicize the epidemic, so that people do not go out. At that time, I felt a bit depressed, like "SARS" , we are all scared, buy things are wearing masks, because there is infectious, feeling more severe than "SARS" . I remember SARS happened when the weather was hot. At that time, I worked in a factory in Shenzhen. I had to wear a mask every day. There were no other restrictions, but at present the whole village is quiet, a lot of people on the Internet also say it feels like jail.

Because in the countryside, there's no such thing as sterilization. There is only a small pharmacy in our village. We go out to wear a good mask, but at present my home has no mask, or daughter-in-law went to the neighbors borrowed 2 back, go out can use. The kids don't have masks, so they stay home every day to remind them to wash their hands.

Epidemic prevention workers at the entrance of a Guang's hometown village (photo taken in February 2020 / A Guang)

Nobody wants that to happen. I'm still a little scared. Now when I see strangers, I try to stay as far away from them as possible, and it feels like it affects everyone. The kids don't know much about it. We adults don't. The children sometimes feel bored, I will read with them, listen to music, play with them. Family doesn't get out much either. If there is no this disease, we are happy new year, can drop by, go around, but out of this matter, we are all stay at home inside. Supermarkets are now sometimes open, sometimes not open, years ago the market there were people, now are quiet.

This outbreak, lasting for a month or two, has not affected us much, so we can buy things on the street. At present, we are running out of steamed bread and vegetables to eat, because we bought some years ago. After the outbreak, we are not allowed to open a market. We can not buy them. If it goes on for months or six months, we won't be able to make it, not just my family, but a lot of families can't afford it, it's been too long, we don't have that much savings, and now I'm just trying to figure out when to go to work.
My son was running after the car... but I had to get out

My Heart's desire is to hope that the children at home to study well, a little better grades. The child's study lets me compare headache, I know the teacher, the parents both also have the responsibility, our educational level is not high, is the elementary school culture, also is has no way. When the kids have problems with their homework, sometimes they ask a neighbor's child, or a neighbor's teacher, or they go back to school to ask the teacher, or sometimes they ask the teacher on wechat how to solve the problem, and then teach the method to the children.

In order to keep in touch with my children, for the past 5 years, I usually go back home during the Spring Festival, but I always return home when I have something to do. If the New Year can not buy train tickets, only bus tickets, too expensive also do not return. When working in Zhuhai, I would video chat with the children for 2 to 3 days, sometimes the children would call me. Every time I went home to see my children, and then returned to Zhuhai, my children were in tears. Once, I went to town to take a train to the city, son in the car chase all the way behind, daughter-in-law also chase after the children running, it was very sad, but no way, have to go out AH.

At present, there is not much land to plant in the countryside either, because of the Southâ€“North Water Transfer Project, the land in the village has to be Green. The land was contracted, my family only two acres of land can be planted, contract land subsidy money a year is about 3000 yuan, also can not be issued on time, no way, can only go out to work. The kids got sick a few years back, and the family ran up some debts, but they paid some of them off over the years, and they still had tens of thousands of dollars. I don't have the skills, I don't have the culture, I work in the factory year after year, I don't know what to do, I don't have any plans, I don't have the capital. Hopefully, the epidemic will pass and everything will be all right.

Social Worker's notes

In the interview process, a light said most one sentence is "has no way" . But can feel, did not have father and mother to take care of him from childhood, to the present home is full of attachment and responsibility. Although he didn't go to school for a few days, he wanted his children to do well, and though he said he had no skills, he did what he could to support his family. In order to survive, he had to endure a long separation from his family. A sudden outbreak of the disease, blocking the return of the work, but also blocking the family's only source of income. Kwong does not know where the future lies, but he still believes: The epidemic has passed, everything will be fine.

Service Recommendations:

Now:

1, to follow up the recent work situation of a Guang to return to the city, if necessary, can provide protection information on the way back to the city, to help him do a good job on the way back to the city security protection.

2. Invite Co authors to participate in online tutoring, interest classes, and other online services for children at home.
3. If necessary, initiate emergency life support for the family.

LONG-TERM:

1. Kwang, who works outside the home and is separated from his wife and children, can be invited to participate in parenting related services and provide counselling on how to maintain close relationships with family members in different places.

2. Have information about career development training and skill learning so that you can invite him to participate and learn more about the job, improve his job skills and expand his employment opportunities.

3. The family's greatest risk is disease. When a family was in debt because their child was sick. Where resources permit, remind them to increase the purchase of appropriate insurance for their children and family members, and enhance the family's risk prevention capacity.
